    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="176"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Wu</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 221.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note, No. 243, of the 29th instant, presenting some considerations why the
                    bill recently passed by Congress prohibiting and regulating the coming of
                    Chinese persons to the territory of the United States should not become a law,
                    and asking that the note be submitted to the President.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to say that a copy of the note has been sent to the
                    President.</p>
                <p>The note was received by the Department after the President had signed the
                    bill.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
